In [219]:
def remove_mileage(x):
        
    if isinstance(x, str) :
        value = x.split(' ')[0]
        if value != '':
            return float(value)        
def get_brand(x):
    return x.split(' ')[0]
In [220]:

df['engine'] = df['engine'].apply(remove_mileage)
df['max_power'] = df['max_power'].apply(remove_mileage)
df['name'] = df['name'].apply(get_brand)

def group_year(year):
    if year > 2015:
        return 'new'
    elif  year > 2010:
        return 'middle'
    else: 
        return 'old'

Which feature is important? and which is not? why?¶

  • This feature are important: year, engine, max_power, seats, fuel,transmission_Manual
  • This feature are not important: name,year,selling_price,km_driven,fuel,seller_type,transmission,owner,mileage,engine,max_power,seats

  • The First if we look at correlation. We gonna see all of this feature have correlation with Selling_price
  • Year: It makes sense that this is important because every year the price of a car decreases due to deterioration.
  • Max Power: max power indicate how fast of this car such as sport cars.
  • Fuel: this is makesense with correlation with Max Power. Petrol's lower price, popular for city driving while Diesel's high price due to efficiency & torque
  • transmission_Manual: Auto more expensive than manual.
  • engine: More engine has more accelerates then more expensive.

I also check feature Important from Model XGB that I got higher accuracy. I got all of this feature that I used.

Which algorithm performs well? Which does not? Why?¶

I got higher accurasy with XGBoost Model. And Low accuracy is linear regression.

Linear regression is a basic model that works well when the data follows a straight, clear pattern. But in real life, data is often messy and complicated, so linear regression can't always give good results.

XGBoost, uses many decision trees to model data more flexibly.It also uses weights and a learning rate to control how each tree contributes, allowing it to adapt better to the structure of real-world data.
